===Idiom===
'''hippity-hop'''

# {{context|childish}} A [[hop]]; to hop; hopping.

====Usage notes====
* This term does not belong to any one part of speech, but rather may be used rather freely as a noun (either countable or uncountable), a verb, an adjective, or an adverb. Its inflections are generally modeled on the noun and verb ''[[hop]]''.
* Frequently used with the verb ''[[go]]'': "He went hippity-hop all the way down the hill."

